{
  "stem": "11089.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was Orthodox, but still, because this rabbi that I mentioned before, [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Oliver ?] Shalom Aharon Teitelbaum-- he was a rabbi of several villages, so we belonged to him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "For example, he used to come every summer to our village to take a bath, you know, this mineral waters, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He used to stay in our place, in my place, in our father's place.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had a big house, and we gave him a room.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So my father would go to him for-- for everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But their view was they were waiting for mashiach as we wait today [? of ?] a more power.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[HEBREW] faith.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "No matter what happened to us, they believed hakol l'tovah It's for good.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It's a hashgacha.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It is God who wants it that way-- that way-- and we have to take it, no matter what.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we didn't dare to go against the rabbi's wish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We didn't-- my father wouldn't go against.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Even so, he understood differently.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He came to this rabbi.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He said to him, I have some money.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I want to go away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I can buy tickets for myself, my family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "This rabbi told him, Mr.-- [INAUDIBLE] [GERMAN] It does not-- it-- it [? doesn't ?] consider us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It will never come to us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It would not reach us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "That was it, and my father didn't move.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So I don't-- I'm not so advanced in-- in knowledge to know what really was behind.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But they believed [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "What will happen will happen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We have to stay where we are.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From the ghetto in Chust, we were taken to a brick factory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there slowly, slowly they-- we went through-- through checking, and they took away whatever we could from us-- they could.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were taken.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
